title: Separator
description: a horizontal or vertical divider between content sections
---

{% from "components/separator/macro.njk" import separator %}

<h2>Horizontal (default)</h2>
<p>A horizontal separator renders an <code>&lt;hr&gt;</code>, which
  assistive tech announces as a thematic break.</p>

<p>Above</p>
{{ separator() }}
<p>Below</p>

<h2>Vertical</h2>
<p>A vertical separator renders
  <code>&lt;div role="separator" aria-orientation="vertical"&gt;</code>
  for screen readers.</p>

<div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--nhsuk-spacing-3);">
  <span>Left</span>
  {{ separator({ orientation: "vertical", label: "Divider" }) }}
  <span>Right</span>
</div>

<h2>With accessible label</h2>
{{ separator({ label: "End of section 1" }) }}
